===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|uncountable|grammar|lang=en}} The [[grammatical mood]] expressing an order (see [[jussive]]). In English, the imperative form of a verb is the same as that of the bare infinitive.
#: ''The verbs in sentences like "Do it!" and "Say what you like!" are in the '''imperative'''.''
# {{context|countable|grammar|lang=en}} A [[verb]] in imperative mood.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} An essential action, a [[must]]: something which is imperative.
#: ''Visiting Berlin is an '''imperative'''.''

